<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-22T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/1296:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-22T12:00:00-04:00">December
                                    22, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 22—11:42
                                a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>241. My telegram No. 229, December 16, 3 p.m. May we have reaction to
                            paragraph No. 2 regarding patrol since Chilean Government formally
                            requested it?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>